  <section>
    <title>Configuring Security Realms</title>

    <para>A security realm is a set of credentials used to access a remote
    server. If you use the same username and password to access Nexus,
    Subversion, and other resources in your environment, your custom Codebase
    would contain a single Security Realm. If you use a different set of
    credentials to access source control and Nexus, you would configure two
    Security Realms. </para>

    <figure id="fig-mse-add-security-realm">
